            <abstract>
                <p>
                    In its “classical form”, the gwǝlt-document has as its core wording something
                    like <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጐለትኩ፡</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወሀብኩ፡ … ጕለ(ተ)፡</foreign> or
                    of the like (ancient variant: <foreign xml:lang="gez">አክሰምኩ፡</foreign> etc.).
                    Many of the documents of this classical type are found in the Liber Axumae or Golden Gospel of Dabra Libānos za-Ham in Eritrea. They are in Geʿez; later in Amharic, or some mix two languages.
                </p>
